propel.core.collections.maps.avl

Class SharedAvlHashtable<TKey extends java.lang.Comparable<TKey>,TValue>

  • java.lang.Object
    • propel.core.collections.maps.avl.SharedAvlHashtable<TKey,TValue>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<KeyValuePair<TKey,TValue>>, ISharedHashtable<TKey,TValue>, ReifiedMap<TKey,TValue>, IShared

    public class SharedAvlHashtable<TKey extends java.lang.Comparable<TKey>,TValue>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISharedHashtable<TKey,TValue>
    A type-aware thread-safe AVL-tree-backed hashtable. This map does not allow null keys to be inserted. Instantiate using e.g.: new SharedAvlHashtable<String, Object>(){}; -OR- new SharedAvlHashtable<String, Object>(String.class, Object.class);

                                             java.lang.Iterable<? extends TValue> values)
        Bulk add key/value pairs to avoid locking/unlocking continuously. Returns true for elements that were successfully added, false for those that were not. You are advised not to use null keys, as these are not allowed and failing will leave the collection in an inconsistent state. This is an O(mlog2(n)) operation where m is the provided element count, n is the hashtables's element Count.
